## Frontend environment example
# Copy this file to `.env.local` in the `frontend/` folder when running locally
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:4000

# Optional: backend-facing service URLs (when useful for local debugging).
# NOTE: Do NOT expose database credentials or internal Redis URLs to the browser
# in production. These examples are for local dev only and are commented out.
#
# Postgres (use the `postgres` service from docker-compose):
# NEXT_PUBLIC_BACKEND_DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:postgres@postgres:5432/mlm?schema=public
#
# Redis (use the `redis` service from docker-compose):
# NEXT_PUBLIC_BACKEND_REDIS_URL=redis://redis:6379
